rdf:Description.lla:note: Ship owner: Thomas Jones, Aberystwith. Voyage from Swansea to Valencia and the Meditarranean coast.
Date of joining ship unreadable due to hole in document, but presumably same as other crew. Last ship may be Alice, registered in Aberystwyth 1860.
Date of joining given as 'do', presumably carried on from top entries despite hole in document.

John Williams was registered in Caernarfon 1860 but there is a John William registered in Aberystwyth 1862, that is probably being referred to. Date of joining given as 'do', presumably carried on from top entries despite hole in document.
Date of joining given as 'do', presumably carried on from top entries despite hole in document. Note by Customs House in Falmouth states that on 1863-01-07 'Thomas Jones was discharged before me'.
Ship Owner: Thomas Jones, Aberystwith. Voyage from Shields to Malaga and Pomeran. Place of birth could also be intended to spell Aberearon, but most likely refers to Aberaeron.
Place of birth probably misheard corruption of Llanrhystud (place of birth on previous record), phonetic spelling, although could refer to Llanerch.
Last ship likely to refer to Premium registered in Shields 1860.
A ship called Birkby was registered in Greenock 1860. A ship called Edward John was registered in Aberystwyth 1860.
Pride of the Ocean was registered in Yarmouth 1860.
Master's certificate no: 42324. Also ship owner. Voyage from Cardiff to Naples.
No record of Anna Bella of Liverpool found in 1860 or 1870.
Diligence was the name of many ships in 1860 including those registered at Aberystwyth and Cardigan.
Leander was a popular name for ships but there was one registered at Aberystwyth which this is likely to refer to.
